technical_skills:
Essential Job Duties or Tasks: 

Benefits
•Manages multiple areas of specialty as a subject matter expert, consultant, and primary point of contact for all benefit related administration.
•Maintains ACE’s benefits plans ensuring compliance with applicable regulations, policies, procedures and provider requirements.
•Reviews and provides updates to all benefit related policies and procedures.
•Manages the annual open enrollment process while providing support required of all levels of staff.
•Oversees benefit data audits for invoice accuracy and retirement and medical benefit compliance.

HR Systems and Data 
•Manages ACE’s HRIS system, UltiPro, and recommends and implements enhancements to the system including data audits, system administration, and vendor management.
•Creates and delivers HR reports, metrics and analytics to support the organizations data needs.
•Ensures HR data is kept current, accurate and readily available to support the invoicing, audit, and compliance processes.

Compensation 
•Manages ACE’s compensation program and ensures that compensation practices are in compliance with federal, state and local legislation.
•Manages the annual salary administration and provides support to ACE managers as needed.

•Ensures HR colleagues are trained on compensation standards and processes.


•Prepares job descriptions and conducts job evaluations and analyses


Other

•Additional duties as assigned


 

Education/Experience/Specialized Knowledge and Competency Requirements:
•Bachelor’s degree in human resources, business, information technology or a related subject.
•Five to eight years of relevant on the job experience
•Experience with a SAAS based HR information system required; UltiPro experience a plus
•Outstanding time management and organizational skills
•Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to interface with all levels of staff
•Professional, self-motivated, and results orientated
•Ability to multi-task and shift priorities in a dynamic environment
•Experience working in a higher education or association environment a plus
